evidence: For medical X-rays, the two dominant processes are the photoelectric effect and Compton scattering.
Traditionally, scattering was treated mainly as a nuisance because it reduces image contrast.
In diagnostic radiology, photoelectric absorption and Compton scattering are the key effects.
For therapeutic applications at higher energies, pair production and photodisintegration also come into play.
